reviewText: I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY ABOUT THIS MOVIE.I SAW IT ON LIFETIME ONCE AND I DON'T KNOW WHAY I THOUGHT I WOULD ENJOY WATCHING IT AGAIN. THIS IS NOT TO SAY THAT THE SERVICE PROVIDED BY YOU WAS NOT THE BEST, BECAUSE IT WAS. THANKS

This movie is about a military man having marital problems, and seeing no way out, making a desperate choice to fake his own death. Gary Cole is a strong lead as the man, and interestingly enough, his wife in real life plays his wife in this movie.
Had seen this movie on Lifetime and remember there was much more to the story than this DVD delivered. Seems to be a poorly edited version, which kept skipping and freezing.
I love Gary Cole he's a great actor. Fun movie to watch on the weekend.
Not the complete movie. This has some scenes left out from the original airing which is disappointing.
I love my DVD, hank you!!
If you like Gary Cole this movie is one of his best. It's a well done movie with great acting.

If you love Gary Cole, you will love this amazing story. I don't want to give anything away, but it is so sad and depressing and weird. The seller was amazing and the movie got here in a very timely manner. Buy this, and you won't be sorry!

If you like cheesy Lifetime movies, this one is great! This movie has a faked death, outrageous lies, schemes that only happen on Lifetime, increasing suspicion, bank robbery, all the good stuff that keeps us coming back to Lifetime movies. It doesn't hurt that Gary Cole is cute too. This movie is so bad it's good.
